|image1    = Tutorial Ascension Tips Equipment Advancement 1.png{{subst:void|<!--$UPLOAD:<<SpriteOutput/TutorialPic/TutorialPage_10006501.png>-<Tutorial Ascension Tips Equipment Advancement 1.png>-<Tutorial Files>>-->}}
|text1     = There are 8 types of basic equipment, and each type corresponds to an attribute. For example:<br />• The Folding Knife can increase On-Field Strength, suitable for on-field damage dealers.<br />• The Peace Pistol can increase Off-Field Strength, suitable for off-field damage dealers.<br />• Roller Skates can increase SPD Amplification, suitable for speed-type characters.
|image2    = Tutorial Ascension Tips Equipment Advancement 2.png{{subst:void|<!--$UPLOAD:<<SpriteOutput/TutorialPic/TutorialPage_10000902.png>-<Tutorial Ascension Tips Equipment Advancement 2.png>-<Tutorial Files>>-->}}
|text2     = The effect of Advanced Equipment is usually related to the effect of the Basic Equipment in its synthesis formula. For example:<br />Folding Knife (On-Field) + Lucky Star (Lucky Strike Rate) = High-frequency Chainsaw (Significantly increases the Lucky Strike Rate of on-field characters)<br />Flower of Life (HP) + Batch Produced Armor (Armor) = Analgesia Chip (When healing a target, reduces the DMG they take)
}}